WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.153 --> 00:00:04.197
<i>MALE NARRATOR:
Previously on</i> Prison Break:

2
00:00:04.221 --> 00:00:05.332
I didn't kill that man. Michael.

3
00:00:05.356 --> 00:00:06.588
The evidence says you did.

4
00:00:06.657 --> 00:00:07.657
I was set up.

5
00:00:09.693 --> 00:00:11.270
<i>POLICEMAN: Put down your weapon.</i>

6
00:00:11.294 --> 00:00:13.979
I find it incumbent that you
see the inside of a prison cell.

7
00:00:14.048 --> 00:00:16.193
I'm looking for someone. A
guy named Lincoln Burrows.

8
00:00:16.217 --> 00:00:17.878
SUCRE: Man killed the
Vice President's brother.

9
00:00:17.902 --> 00:00:19.512
Why you want to see
Burrows so bad anyhow?

10
00:00:19.536 --> 00:00:20.713
<i>SCOFIELD: Because
he's my brother.</i>

11
00:00:20.737 --> 00:00:22.070
I'm getting you out of here.

12
00:00:22.139 --> 00:00:25.224
It's impossible. Not if you
designed the place. it isn't.

13
00:00:25.292 --> 00:00:27.626
You've seen the
blueprints. Better than that.

14
00:00:27.695 --> 00:00:29.878
I've got them on me.

15
00:00:29.947 --> 00:00:31.858
JENAE: I took some time
to speak to your mother...

16
00:00:31.882 --> 00:00:33.893
Hey. if you're talking
about that guy at Fox River...

17
00:00:33.917 --> 00:00:35.334
He refuses to
call him his father.

18
00:00:35.402 --> 00:00:37.453
Take the only thing
Burrows has left.

19
00:00:37.538 --> 00:00:41.473
<i>The chair isn't the only way
to take a man's life in prison.</i>

20
00:00:41.542 --> 00:00:43.686
<i>FEMALE NARRATOR: And now
scenes from last week's episode.</i>

21
00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:45.372
But constantly coming
up here for count

22
00:00:45.396 --> 00:00:47.741
<i>won't let me do what I need
to do to get through that wall.</i>

23
00:00:47.765 --> 00:00:50.093
SUCRE: Only way to
stop count is a lockdown.

24
00:00:50.117 --> 00:00:53.018
You gotta get the
inmates riled up.

25
00:00:53.087 --> 00:00:55.203
All right. that's it! Lockdown!

26
00:00:55.272 --> 00:00:56.632
Somebody made an
anonymous phone call.

27
00:00:56.656 --> 00:00:58.385
Whoever made that call
couldn't have seen Lincoln.

28
00:00:58.409 --> 00:00:59.624
How do you know?

29
00:00:59.693 --> 00:01:01.555
Because the phone call
came from Washington. D.C.

30
00:01:01.579 --> 00:01:03.561
(INMATES LAUGHING)

31
00:01:03.630 --> 00:01:06.131
This is Bellick. Our
wing has been breached.

32
00:01:07.268 --> 00:01:08.928
Hooke's law of elasticity?

33
00:01:08.952 --> 00:01:11.014
If we drill holes in
strategic locations.

34
00:01:11.038 --> 00:01:13.622
we compromise the
load-carrying capacity of the wall.

35
00:01:13.707 --> 00:01:14.956
Take the cuffs off.

36
00:01:15.025 --> 00:01:16.525
A rookie CO.

37
00:01:16.594 --> 00:01:18.110
LINCOLN: Get out of here. T-Bag.

38
00:01:18.179 --> 00:01:19.894
I think we can
work something out.

39
00:01:19.963 --> 00:01:21.213
No deal.

40
00:01:24.618 --> 00:01:25.812
<i>TANCREDI: Where's my daughter?</i>

41
00:01:25.836 --> 00:01:27.130
<i>POPE: Not to
worry. sir. She's fine.</i>

42
00:01:27.154 --> 00:01:29.015
A guard there assures
us that everything is fine.

43
00:01:29.039 --> 00:01:30.800
We have everything
under control. Governor.

44
00:01:30.824 --> 00:01:32.307
You better hope you do.

45
00:01:32.393 --> 00:01:34.125
(INMATES CLAMORING)

46
00:01:36.213 --> 00:01:38.012
They're breaking out.

47
00:01:39.150 --> 00:01:40.350
They're breaking...

48
00:01:42.036 --> 00:01:43.552
(SHUSHING)

49
00:01:43.621 --> 00:01:44.786
We need a favor.

50
00:01:44.855 --> 00:01:46.482
Some heavy hitters
want this done.

51
00:01:46.506 --> 00:01:48.017
TURK: Burrows
is as good as dead.

52
00:01:48.041 --> 00:01:49.385
TURK: You looking for Scofield?

53
00:01:49.409 --> 00:01:51.289
Yeah. Turk. Come on.

54
00:01:52.830 --> 00:01:55.113
Hey. yo. Stroker's
about to get the Doc.

55
00:01:59.836 --> 00:02:02.020
Sucre. I need you to
finish what we started.

56
00:02:02.088 --> 00:02:04.473
No one touches the CO. No one.

57
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:12.074
-== [ www.OpenSubtitles.org ] ==-

58
00:02:16.870 --> 00:02:18.236
(INMATES SCREAMING)

59
00:02:32.669 --> 00:02:35.865
<i>POLICEMAN: (ON LOUDSPEAKER) Attention
all personnel. Attention all personnel.</i>

60
00:02:35.889 --> 00:02:37.689
<i>Secure the perimeter.</i>

61
00:02:39.909 --> 00:02:41.793
<i>On all areas.</i>

62
00:02:41.862 --> 00:02:45.330
<i>Attention. The area
is on secure lockdown.</i>

63
00:03:02.265 --> 00:03:04.365
<i>(MAN CHATTERING ON LOUDSPEAKER)</i>

64
00:03:15.044 --> 00:03:17.429
(SOLDIERS CHATTERING)

65
00:03:18.732 --> 00:03:21.178
Any word from the
Governor? Not yet. boss.

66
00:03:21.202 --> 00:03:22.301
(SIRENS WAILING)

67
00:03:22.369 --> 00:03:23.369
(ALARM BUZZING)

68
00:03:23.436 --> 00:03:26.271
Bellick. get those guys in line.

69
00:03:26.340 --> 00:03:28.206
Get them into formation.

70
00:03:28.275 --> 00:03:30.286
We going back in? Not yet.

71
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:32.571
We cut the water off
about an hour ago.

72
00:03:32.595 --> 00:03:34.590
The stink alone should
drive them out of there.

73
00:03:34.614 --> 00:03:38.182
You think that's gonna
work? No. but it's protocol.

74
00:03:38.251 --> 00:03:40.463
And we're all gonna
do this by the book.

75
00:03:40.487 --> 00:03:42.848
It's the best chance we have
of everybody getting out of there

76
00:03:42.872 --> 00:03:44.992
without getting hurt.
FIORELLO: Hey!

77
00:03:48.928 --> 00:03:52.013
<i>This is the Warden.
What's happening in there?</i>

78
00:03:52.082 --> 00:03:54.165
We got some demands!

79
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:56.685
Tell them we need
the air back on.

80
00:03:56.754 --> 00:03:58.437
We need the AC.

81
00:03:59.339 --> 00:04:01.372
We got a hostage. A guard.

82
00:04:02.809 --> 00:04:05.176
We got a hostage. the new guard.

83
00:04:07.514 --> 00:04:09.464
Find out who's in there.

84
00:04:17.490 --> 00:04:19.658
They got Bob.

85
00:04:19.726 --> 00:04:23.779
And that girl doctor.
Tell them we got her.

86
00:04:23.847 --> 00:04:25.514
Why don't you do it?

87
00:04:25.582 --> 00:04:27.582
I don't want to get shot.

88
00:04:30.737 --> 00:04:33.254
And we got the girl doctor!

89
00:04:33.323 --> 00:04:36.041
The doctor? There's only one.

90
00:04:36.109 --> 00:04:39.927
How the hell did that happen?
How did they get their hands on her?

91
00:04:39.996 --> 00:04:41.958
I thought she was safe.
She was in Sick Bay.

92
00:04:41.982 --> 00:04:44.744
We got to get her out of there.
Somebody has got to go in there now.

93
00:04:44.768 --> 00:04:46.918
We can't do it. sir. Why not?

94
00:04:47.638 --> 00:04:49.454
It's not by the book.

95
00:05:00.684 --> 00:05:03.118
Sir. I've got some
updates for you.

96
00:05:08.625 --> 00:05:12.994
Help! Help!

97
00:05:26.226 --> 00:05:28.459
LINCOLN: Scofield's in here?

98
00:05:28.528 --> 00:05:30.228
(GROANS)

99
00:05:30.297 --> 00:05:32.164
You sure he's in here?

100
00:05:34.301 --> 00:05:35.833
(STEAM HISSING)

101
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:42.040
Turk? Turk?

102
00:05:52.436 --> 00:05:53.701
(CHOKING)

103
00:05:54.871 --> 00:05:56.187
(GRUNTING)

104
00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:32.707
(GRUNTING)

105
00:07:00.287 --> 00:07:01.503
(COUGHS)

106
00:07:17.688 --> 00:07:19.688
You ain't gonna use that.

107
00:07:20.991 --> 00:07:23.775
You making up the rules now?

108
00:07:23.843 --> 00:07:25.588
It's my house.
You got a problem?

109
00:07:25.612 --> 00:07:28.179
Yeah. I got a
problem. We all do.

110
00:07:28.248 --> 00:07:31.583
I'm not a problem.
I swear to God.

111
00:07:32.719 --> 00:07:35.487
I'm not gonna say anything.

112
00:07:35.556 --> 00:07:38.740
I didn't see anything.
That's right. badge.

113
00:07:38.809 --> 00:07:40.709
You didn't see nothing.

114
00:07:42.329 --> 00:07:44.812
Wait. Don't leave.

115
00:07:48.935 --> 00:07:51.535
Sorry. I'll be back.

116
00:07:53.456 --> 00:07:56.057
Don't worry. I'll cover for you.

117
00:07:56.743 --> 00:07:58.460
(INMATES CLAMORING)

118
00:08:03.433 --> 00:08:07.518
Don't worry. CO. all right?
I'm not gonna hurt nobody.

119
00:08:08.555 --> 00:08:10.538
I'm part of the team now.

120
00:08:15.746 --> 00:08:19.264
Help a brother
out. Drag that over.

121
00:08:24.087 --> 00:08:25.653
That's the way.

122
00:08:25.722 --> 00:08:27.455
Mmm. mmm. mmm. hmm.

123
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.136
(VENT CLANGING)

124
00:09:06.596 --> 00:09:07.895
Ladies and gentlemen.

125
00:09:07.964 --> 00:09:10.598
please return to your seats
and fasten your seatbelts.

126
00:09:10.667 --> 00:09:13.968
We're making our final
approach into Washington. D.C.

127
00:09:16.389 --> 00:09:18.956
We need to focus
on the real question.

128
00:09:19.025 --> 00:09:21.226
Who wanted Terrence
Steadman dead?

129
00:09:21.294 --> 00:09:24.229
The call came from D.C.
What does that tell you?

130
00:09:24.297 --> 00:09:26.537
You got to think
past the government.

131
00:09:26.583 --> 00:09:30.518
Anybody could be here. A...
a business partner. a rival.

132
00:09:30.587 --> 00:09:32.353
Before Steadman was killed.

133
00:09:32.422 --> 00:09:36.624
Ecofield introduced a prototype
electric engine at the techno conference.

134
00:09:36.693 --> 00:09:38.826
$60 barrels of oil
would be obsolete

135
00:09:38.895 --> 00:09:41.562
if that thing ever
hit the mainstream.

136
00:09:41.631 --> 00:09:44.348
Could be oil. oil companies.

137
00:09:44.418 --> 00:09:47.418
Suppliers. consumers.
everything in between.

138
00:09:48.588 --> 00:09:51.389
Or the government of
an oil-based economy.

139
00:09:52.676 --> 00:09:55.010
Like the United States.

140
00:09:55.078 --> 00:09:57.111
Can I take your soda? Sure.

141
00:09:57.180 --> 00:09:59.420
Thank you. Thank you.

142
00:10:00.617 --> 00:10:03.635
At any rate. we land.
we meet my guy.

143
00:10:03.703 --> 00:10:06.449
And even if we don't find the
person who tipped off the cops.

144
00:10:06.473 --> 00:10:07.972
we find his phone.

145
00:10:08.041 --> 00:10:09.941
The paper trail begins.

146
00:10:10.861 --> 00:10:12.577
(INMATES CLAMORING)

147
00:10:20.336 --> 00:10:23.971
STROKER: Only a matter of
time. Doc. Only a matter of time.

148
00:10:28.211 --> 00:10:30.394
Help!

149
00:11:15.692 --> 00:11:17.291
(SIRENS WAILING)

150
00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:37.011
(REPORTERS CHATTERING)

151
00:11:53.112 --> 00:11:55.847
That's the Governor.

152
00:11:55.915 --> 00:11:58.155
Whatever happens.
don't say anything.

153
00:12:22.859 --> 00:12:25.738
Governor. appreciate your
coming. Now. you should know.

154
00:12:25.762 --> 00:12:27.940
since our conversation.
the situation has escalated.

155
00:12:27.964 --> 00:12:30.426
But not to worry. We're making
good progress with our contacts.

156
00:12:30.450 --> 00:12:34.151
Just cut the crap. Warden. and
tell me where my daughter is.

157
00:12:39.509 --> 00:12:40.858
Help!

158
00:12:44.798 --> 00:12:46.314
Help!

159
00:12:46.383 --> 00:12:50.351
T-BAG: What have we got
here? "Tyler Robert Hudson."

160
00:12:50.419 --> 00:12:52.870
That is fancy. CO.

161
00:12:52.939 --> 00:12:55.756
Oh. look at that
address. "144 Oak Park..."

162
00:12:56.759 --> 00:12:58.158
What's this?

163
00:12:58.978 --> 00:13:00.395
Terrace.

164
00:13:00.463 --> 00:13:03.197
Terrace. How do
you swing that. CO?

165
00:13:03.266 --> 00:13:07.001
Sounds like you're about
something. living on a terrace.

166
00:13:08.888 --> 00:13:12.040
I can't wait to kick it
on a terrace. What?

167
00:13:13.293 --> 00:13:15.493
Oh. oh.

168
00:13:15.562 --> 00:13:18.595
This here must be your
daughter. Put it back.

169
00:13:18.664 --> 00:13:19.763
Prom?

170
00:13:24.271 --> 00:13:27.571
You know what they say
about a prom dress. don't you?

171
00:13:31.477 --> 00:13:34.178
She ain't come home
that night. did she?

172
00:13:35.498 --> 00:13:39.250
No. she wore
that all night long.

173
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:43.988
Next morning.

174
00:13:44.057 --> 00:13:47.241
she had to throw that dress in
the trash can behind the motel

175
00:13:47.309 --> 00:13:50.628
so her mama didn't see
the... ABRUZZI: Hey. hey. hey!

176
00:13:51.898 --> 00:13:53.508
What the hell are you doing?

177
00:13:53.532 --> 00:13:57.184
I'm just kicking it with Deputy
Dawg. You know. talking women.

178
00:13:58.988 --> 00:14:00.788
I'll be very clear here.

179
00:14:00.857 --> 00:14:04.692
because you and I
face an evolutionary gap.

180
00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:10.148
You ain't gonna hurt this man.

181
00:14:10.217 --> 00:14:13.885
We're locked into this
thing now. Understand?

182
00:14:16.255 --> 00:14:18.690
And he's the only
leverage we have.

183
00:14:24.164 --> 00:14:26.163
Thank you. You're welcome.

184
00:14:28.234 --> 00:14:31.619
Now. do we have
an understanding?

185
00:14:31.687 --> 00:14:37.575
I'm on your side now. You understand
me? I'm just going with the flow.

186
00:14:37.643 --> 00:14:41.229
You let me know when you're
done with your. uh. leverage.

187
00:15:00.866 --> 00:15:02.216
Let me out!

188
00:15:08.808 --> 00:15:10.807
Let's smoke the bitch out!

189
00:15:12.429 --> 00:15:14.062
(INMATE WHOOPING)

190
00:15:23.506 --> 00:15:26.123
SARA: Help!

191
00:15:31.263 --> 00:15:32.930
(INMATES YELLING)

192
00:15:36.335 --> 00:15:38.469
What are you gonna do now. Doc?

193
00:15:38.537 --> 00:15:39.871
(INMATE LAUGHING)

194
00:15:47.313 --> 00:15:49.012
(YELLING)

195
00:15:50.283 --> 00:15:53.384
It ain't gonna hurt real
bad if you make it easy.

196
00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:55.653
If you make it hard. though...

197
00:15:56.989 --> 00:15:58.323
(GROANING)

198
00:15:59.942 --> 00:16:02.160
Open the door! Come here!

199
00:16:02.228 --> 00:16:04.929
I said. open the
door! Open the door!

200
00:16:04.998 --> 00:16:07.531
Come on. Grab my hand.

201
00:16:08.585 --> 00:16:09.817
Come on!

202
00:16:15.525 --> 00:16:19.177
STROKER: Come here. Open the door.
Come here. Open this door. Come here.

203
00:16:23.666 --> 00:16:24.916
I've got you.

204
00:16:31.057 --> 00:16:32.439
(PANTING)

205
00:16:34.059 --> 00:16:37.445
You all right? It's okay.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

206
00:16:40.316 --> 00:16:43.967
See these pipes? We're
gonna stay on them.

207
00:16:44.036 --> 00:16:46.336
They go through the
wall and over the hallway.

208
00:16:46.405 --> 00:16:48.689
and they're gonna
get us out of here.

209
00:16:48.757 --> 00:16:51.058
All you have to do is follow me.

210
00:16:51.928 --> 00:16:53.627
Okay? Yeah.

211
00:16:53.696 --> 00:16:56.097
Okay. Let's go.

212
00:17:06.925 --> 00:17:08.459
Where'd she go?

213
00:17:12.231 --> 00:17:13.597
(CHUCKLING)

214
00:17:24.893 --> 00:17:26.138
VERONICA: Where
are we meeting him?

215
00:17:26.162 --> 00:17:28.140
NICK: Georgetown.
in a parking garage.

216
00:17:28.164 --> 00:17:29.463
He's a private investigator.

217
00:17:29.532 --> 00:17:32.266
He used to be my roommate.
freshman year at Duke.

218
00:17:34.437 --> 00:17:36.281
<i>MALE REPORTER: The
disturbance has escalated...</i>

219
00:17:36.305 --> 00:17:38.021
Oh. my God. Nick. look.

220
00:17:38.090 --> 00:17:40.540
<i>At least two hostages
have been confirmed</i>

221
00:17:40.609 --> 00:17:43.377
<i>in what is now being
called a full-scale riot</i>

222
00:17:43.445 --> 00:17:45.896
<i>here at the Fox River
State Penitentiary.</i>

223
00:17:45.965 --> 00:17:48.282
Should we go
back. or keep going?

224
00:17:48.350 --> 00:17:51.536
We should keep going.

225
00:17:51.604 --> 00:17:53.949
You want to go back and stand
there with the rest of the people

226
00:17:53.973 --> 00:17:55.706
who aren't helping?

227
00:17:57.009 --> 00:17:58.592
Come on.

228
00:17:58.661 --> 00:18:00.439
<i>MALE REPORTER: The
National Guard responded</i>

229
00:18:00.463 --> 00:18:02.141
<i>after Illinois Governor
Frank Tancredi</i>

230
00:18:02.165 --> 00:18:03.997
<i>declared a state of emergency...</i>

231
00:18:04.066 --> 00:18:06.845
Come on. honey. it's time
to go. Hold on. Hold on.

232
00:18:06.869 --> 00:18:09.630
<i>No word on what caused the
initial disturbance. but sources...</i>

233
00:18:09.672 --> 00:18:11.322
That's not Fox River. is it?

234
00:18:11.374 --> 00:18:13.885
<i>Corrections say tensions
often run high at this facility.</i>

235
00:18:13.909 --> 00:18:16.010
<i>Fox River is a
level-five institution</i>

236
00:18:16.079 --> 00:18:17.906
<i>housing some of the
most dangerous criminals...</i>

237
00:18:17.930 --> 00:18:19.947
What are you doing?
We have to go. Come on.

238
00:18:20.015 --> 00:18:21.732
No. Dad might be in trouble.

239
00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:25.352
Your father's already in trouble.
There's nothing we can do about it.

240
00:18:26.588 --> 00:18:29.423
Just don't make a scene. okay?

241
00:18:29.491 --> 00:18:32.827
He gets very uncomfortable
with this thing. Just...

242
00:18:32.895 --> 00:18:36.981
Let's just go. okay?
Please. Oh. God forbid. man!

243
00:18:37.050 --> 00:18:40.985
We're just talking about
my old man here. and his life.

244
00:18:41.053 --> 00:18:43.693
If... if that's all right with
you. Leave me out of this.

245
00:18:43.723 --> 00:18:45.239
I am leaving you out of it.

246
00:18:45.307 --> 00:18:47.919
I left you out of it the day
I met you. Okay... okay.

247
00:18:47.943 --> 00:18:50.663
Because nothing in her life or
mine has anything to do with you.

248
00:18:50.730 --> 00:18:52.941
I'm gonna pretend I didn't
hear that. Oh. yeah? Or what?

249
00:18:52.965 --> 00:18:54.543
ADRIAN: You see? This
is what I'm talking about.

250
00:18:54.567 --> 00:18:56.311
This is the kind of
crap I have to deal with.

251
00:18:56.335 --> 00:18:58.864
Just let me handle it! The kind
of crap you have to deal with?

252
00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:00.366
LJ. you want to
talk to me. you talk...

253
00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:03.056
Oh. you got no clue. do you?

254
00:19:03.142 --> 00:19:05.092
Honey... Leave me alone!

255
00:19:05.160 --> 00:19:06.872
Get off me! What the
hell are you doing?

256
00:19:06.896 --> 00:19:08.773
You don't talk to your
mother like that. Stop it!

257
00:19:08.797 --> 00:19:10.564
Take that. boy. Stop.

258
00:19:13.069 --> 00:19:15.586
Go upstairs. LJ. now!

259
00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:17.104
Go!

260
00:19:17.173 --> 00:19:19.134
You love that man? Just go.

261
00:19:19.158 --> 00:19:21.492
You love that
man? Do what I say.

262
00:19:32.288 --> 00:19:33.804
(LINCOLN COUGHING)

263
00:19:46.502 --> 00:19:47.835
Turk.

264
00:19:47.904 --> 00:19:50.488
(HOARSELY) Why are
you doing this? I was sent to.

265
00:19:51.157 --> 00:19:52.756
Why? Why?

266
00:20:00.683 --> 00:20:02.032
(THUDDING)

267
00:20:29.095 --> 00:20:33.297
Why'd you do this? What's
it all about? Who sent you?

268
00:20:33.366 --> 00:20:37.434
Man. you got to help
me. You've got to. Please.

269
00:20:40.022 --> 00:20:41.138
Talk!

270
00:20:58.858 --> 00:21:00.608
(PRAYING IN SPANISH)

271
00:21:15.090 --> 00:21:19.026
Who's your friend?
Scared the hell out of me.

272
00:21:19.095 --> 00:21:23.096
Who you talking to?
It's the Fish's idea.

273
00:21:23.165 --> 00:21:26.165
The devil marks the wall so
you know where to drill the holes.

274
00:21:26.202 --> 00:21:28.364
You're making holes
with an eggbeater?

275
00:21:28.388 --> 00:21:30.470
I know. Crazy. huh?

276
00:21:30.539 --> 00:21:32.506
It's called the Hooker law.

277
00:21:32.575 --> 00:21:36.376
It says that if you poke the exact
right holes in something big and strong.

278
00:21:36.445 --> 00:21:38.129
it gets very weak.

279
00:21:38.931 --> 00:21:40.965
That's true.

280
00:21:41.017 --> 00:21:43.851
When the wall is weak.
we can take it down.

281
00:21:45.237 --> 00:21:47.338
At least. that's the plan.

282
00:21:47.406 --> 00:21:49.890
Yeah. that's always the plan.

283
00:21:52.111 --> 00:21:55.846
You should never
underestimate a wall.

284
00:21:55.915 --> 00:22:00.434
You see. sometimes no
matter how hard you try.

285
00:22:00.519 --> 00:22:02.836
it just won't give in.

286
00:22:09.629 --> 00:22:11.128
(SARA PANTING)

287
00:22:15.535 --> 00:22:18.135
Are you all right?
I'm okay. I'm fine.

288
00:22:22.858 --> 00:22:24.491
Come look this way!

289
00:22:24.560 --> 00:22:26.961
(INMATES CLAMORING)

290
00:22:29.065 --> 00:22:31.065
Open up!

291
00:22:33.902 --> 00:22:36.781
You know what? I
need a minute. I'm sorry.

292
00:22:36.805 --> 00:22:39.974
It's not much
further. Just a sec.

293
00:22:40.042 --> 00:22:42.926
You know. we can stop if
you want. Catch your breath.

294
00:22:42.978 --> 00:22:45.746
Okay. Yeah. I
could use a minute.

295
00:22:47.316 --> 00:22:49.299
Come here. girl. Come here.

296
00:22:49.368 --> 00:22:52.553
Things should be
winding down around now.

297
00:22:52.622 --> 00:22:54.466
Pretty soon the powers
that be will break in

298
00:22:54.490 --> 00:22:56.857
and it'll all be over.

299
00:22:56.925 --> 00:22:59.025
It's just a matter of time.

300
00:22:59.862 --> 00:23:01.962
What's happening in A-Wing?

301
00:23:03.999 --> 00:23:07.033
All hell's breaking loose.

302
00:23:07.102 --> 00:23:10.270
But I think if we stay up
here. we should be okay.

303
00:23:12.007 --> 00:23:14.308
I can't believe
this is happening.

304
00:23:14.394 --> 00:23:17.912
Yeah. come here.
That's real good. Doc.

305
00:23:17.980 --> 00:23:20.480
You know. I'm fishing. girl.

306
00:23:20.549 --> 00:23:22.249
I know you want it. girl.

307
00:23:27.690 --> 00:23:29.607
You ever been to Baja?

308
00:23:30.576 --> 00:23:33.477
Mexico? No.

309
00:23:33.546 --> 00:23:36.230
There's this great
place down there.

310
00:23:36.298 --> 00:23:37.697
$20 a night.

311
00:23:38.501 --> 00:23:40.501
hammock on the back deck.

312
00:23:41.403 --> 00:23:43.153
Beers are 50 cents.

313
00:23:44.239 --> 00:23:46.139
25 cents at happy hour.

314
00:23:49.779 --> 00:23:52.479
Ever been to Thailand?
Thailand is great.

315
00:23:52.548 --> 00:23:56.967
Michael. if you're trying to calm
me down. you're doing a terrible job.

316
00:23:57.036 --> 00:23:58.619
But I am trying.

317
00:23:59.422 --> 00:24:00.503
Shh.

318
00:24:01.540 --> 00:24:02.540
You hear that?

319
00:24:03.709 --> 00:24:06.143
Why are you here?
What do you mean?

320
00:24:08.430 --> 00:24:11.632
Crawling around in the
ceiling. risking your life.

321
00:24:11.701 --> 00:24:15.636
You needed help and.
uh. I came to find you.

322
00:24:21.994 --> 00:24:24.128
How did you know where to go?

323
00:24:27.650 --> 00:24:29.250
When everything
went off in A-Wing.

324
00:24:29.285 --> 00:24:32.352
the COs left the station
and I saw you on the monitor.

325
00:24:32.421 --> 00:24:36.574
One of my first assignments on PI.
we were up here cleaning out toxic mold.

326
00:24:36.642 --> 00:24:39.993
It took days. so I'm kind
of familiar with the layout.

327
00:24:41.664 --> 00:24:43.463
Hope you wore a mask.

328
00:24:44.417 --> 00:24:47.151
Excuse me? To
prevent inhalation.

329
00:24:47.219 --> 00:24:49.686
Mold can be really dangerous.

330
00:24:49.755 --> 00:24:51.855
Yeah. I wore a mask.

331
00:24:59.365 --> 00:25:01.499
Get up there. get up there.

332
00:25:05.821 --> 00:25:09.673
The door to the Visitation
Room. do you ever use it?

333
00:25:09.742 --> 00:25:12.887
Um. not usually. But my
access card should work.

334
00:25:12.911 --> 00:25:14.811
STROKER: Get up. MAN: Yeah.

335
00:25:17.850 --> 00:25:19.082
Come on.

336
00:25:20.185 --> 00:25:22.019
Let's go. Move.

337
00:25:24.407 --> 00:25:25.922
Come on. baby.

338
00:25:33.716 --> 00:25:35.532
STROKER: Get up there. man.

339
00:25:40.572 --> 00:25:41.621
Let's go!

340
00:25:45.895 --> 00:25:46.895
Come here!

341
00:25:51.183 --> 00:25:54.752
Yes. sir. I understand. But
believe me. Sara is our top priority.

342
00:25:54.804 --> 00:25:56.203
The hell she is.

343
00:25:56.272 --> 00:25:59.039
I ordered a state of
emergency an hour ago.

344
00:25:59.108 --> 00:26:00.428
Soldier. SOLDIER: Yes. sir?

345
00:26:00.475 --> 00:26:02.220
Get me your commanding
officer. Right away. sir.

346
00:26:02.244 --> 00:26:04.156
Now. what the hell
is going on out here?

347
00:26:04.180 --> 00:26:06.641
Negotiating. sir. They
can't hold out much longer.

348
00:26:06.665 --> 00:26:07.981
Negotiating?

349
00:26:08.050 --> 00:26:10.328
It is 100 degrees in there.
They're almost out of water.

350
00:26:10.352 --> 00:26:12.330
We are trying to avoid
doing anything extreme.

351
00:26:12.354 --> 00:26:15.989
Look. I don't care if it takes a
massacre to get her out of there.

352
00:26:16.058 --> 00:26:19.410
Do you understand me? Now.
if you're not gonna do it. I am.

353
00:26:19.478 --> 00:26:20.856
Sir. Captain.

354
00:26:20.880 --> 00:26:24.114
Spread the news.
you're going in. Yes. sir.

355
00:26:24.183 --> 00:26:26.316
It's time to do this my way.

356
00:26:30.155 --> 00:26:31.871
(INMATES SCREAMING)

357
00:26:43.569 --> 00:26:44.901
All right.

358
00:27:03.372 --> 00:27:04.705
I got you.

359
00:27:14.616 --> 00:27:16.600
Hey. Fish!

360
00:27:16.669 --> 00:27:19.035
You gonna keep that
nurse all to yourself?

361
00:27:27.096 --> 00:27:28.362
(CHOKING)

362
00:27:30.215 --> 00:27:31.547
(BOTH GRUNTING)

363
00:27:42.027 --> 00:27:43.126
Stop!

364
00:27:46.799 --> 00:27:48.448
(POP POP SCREAMING)

365
00:27:52.087 --> 00:27:54.171
Oh. my knee!

366
00:27:55.725 --> 00:27:57.407
SARA: Come on. This way.

367
00:28:16.946 --> 00:28:19.880
Good call. Governor.
bringing in the big guns.

368
00:28:19.949 --> 00:28:23.150
Appreciate your support.
Captain Brad Bellick.

369
00:28:24.937 --> 00:28:28.889
I sent you a letter earlier this
year. My views on penal reform.

370
00:28:28.958 --> 00:28:32.025
Oh. And what are they?

371
00:28:32.094 --> 00:28:36.463
These inmates don't mess
around. us CO's need to get tough.

372
00:28:36.532 --> 00:28:38.627
Warden Pope's a good
guy. don't get me wrong.

373
00:28:38.651 --> 00:28:40.261
But he doesn't
understand that sometimes

374
00:28:40.285 --> 00:28:43.620
you got to grab the situation
by the gonads and take control.

375
00:28:43.688 --> 00:28:45.383
And is that what you
would do. Captain?

376
00:28:45.407 --> 00:28:47.674
Yes. sir. that's
exactly what I'd do.

377
00:28:47.743 --> 00:28:48.842
So...

378
00:28:57.152 --> 00:28:59.402
Give me that. give me that.

379
00:28:59.471 --> 00:29:01.605
I don't know. I...
Give me that thing.

380
00:29:01.674 --> 00:29:04.691
Demolition runs in the family.

381
00:29:04.759 --> 00:29:07.643
The whole trick is pressure.

382
00:29:07.712 --> 00:29:09.896
Where should I... Here? Yeah.

383
00:29:09.965 --> 00:29:11.198
Good. good.

384
00:29:11.266 --> 00:29:14.334
You see. you should
push hard but not too hard.

385
00:29:14.403 --> 00:29:16.247
Just like when you're. you know.

386
00:29:16.271 --> 00:29:17.983
Yeah. but you got
to be careful. though.

387
00:29:18.007 --> 00:29:19.917
Yeah. yeah. I know. I
know. No. no. I mean it.

388
00:29:19.941 --> 00:29:22.120
(STUTTERING) One slip.
and you'll hit the gas pipe.

389
00:29:22.144 --> 00:29:23.727
Gas pipe?

390
00:29:23.795 --> 00:29:26.880
Yeah. you know. As in.
pipe that carries the gas.

391
00:29:39.077 --> 00:29:40.611
We can't go this way.

392
00:29:40.663 --> 00:29:43.313
We have to. There's no
other way to Visitation.

393
00:29:43.381 --> 00:29:45.332
This is it. No. it's not.

394
00:29:47.152 --> 00:29:49.286
It's back this way.
This won't help.

395
00:29:49.354 --> 00:29:51.132
Trust me. Michael.
if you're wrong...

396
00:29:51.156 --> 00:29:52.889
We don't have time.

397
00:30:00.115 --> 00:30:03.683
Not too hard. not too soft...

398
00:30:05.253 --> 00:30:07.453
When I was her age.
I had such bad skin.

399
00:30:07.522 --> 00:30:08.855
(EXCLAIMS)

400
00:30:10.626 --> 00:30:12.442
Acne. they called it.

401
00:30:14.830 --> 00:30:18.548
Yeah. she looks just like all
them girls who made fun of me.

402
00:30:20.518 --> 00:30:23.053
After I kill you.

403
00:30:23.121 --> 00:30:26.722
I'm gonna crawl out that hole
and call me up a limousine.

404
00:30:26.791 --> 00:30:29.526
and me and your
baby's going to the prom.

405
00:30:35.534 --> 00:30:36.849
(SNICKERS)

406
00:30:51.567 --> 00:30:53.600
Captain. what's
the news with Sara?

407
00:30:53.669 --> 00:30:55.063
Still trying to find her. sir.

408
00:30:55.087 --> 00:30:56.531
You don't even
know where she is?

409
00:30:56.555 --> 00:31:00.239
We're on it. As soon as
we do. we'll let you know.

410
00:31:00.308 --> 00:31:03.961
I should've listened to Captain
Bellick and gassed the whole block.

411
00:31:04.029 --> 00:31:05.545
Captain Bellick?

412
00:31:05.614 --> 00:31:08.331
He's right on the frontline. He
knows what these guys can do.

413
00:31:08.400 --> 00:31:11.434
You better pray that Sara
gets out of there in one piece.

414
00:31:11.503 --> 00:31:14.371
I do. Governor. but
this is still my prison.

415
00:31:14.439 --> 00:31:17.607
Whatever happens. I
take full responsibility.

416
00:31:18.410 --> 00:31:19.726
Excuse me.

417
00:31:31.957 --> 00:31:33.623
It's this way.

418
00:31:33.692 --> 00:31:35.375
(GRUNTING) Yeah.

419
00:31:36.445 --> 00:31:37.511
Ooh.

420
00:31:38.180 --> 00:31:40.347
Yes. We're through.

421
00:31:42.951 --> 00:31:45.585
Time to put this
theory to the test.

422
00:31:45.654 --> 00:31:48.321
I guess we start
chipping away now.

423
00:31:48.390 --> 00:31:51.758
Right on. She's all yours. pal.

424
00:32:13.348 --> 00:32:14.947
(LAUGHING)

425
00:32:20.272 --> 00:32:22.338
This is about right.

426
00:32:23.875 --> 00:32:25.208
We did it.

427
00:32:28.480 --> 00:32:29.813
That's it.

428
00:32:31.317 --> 00:32:32.799
Wait. I can't leave you here.

429
00:32:32.867 --> 00:32:36.069
You don't have a choice. I'm
one of the bad guys. remember?

430
00:32:36.137 --> 00:32:38.104
INMATE: Over there! Go. go. go!

431
00:32:38.173 --> 00:32:39.973
INMATE 1: Come
on. man. Let's move it!

432
00:32:40.008 --> 00:32:41.128
INMATE 2: Check this out.

433
00:32:46.832 --> 00:32:48.543
<i>MAN: (ON RADIO) Can
you see the assailant?</i>

434
00:32:48.567 --> 00:32:51.601
Number eight. Affirmative.
I've got him in sight.

435
00:32:53.522 --> 00:32:56.122
What are you gonna do?

436
00:32:56.191 --> 00:32:58.991
Go back to my cell.
Stay out of the way.

437
00:32:59.061 --> 00:33:00.860
Michael. What?

438
00:33:03.365 --> 00:33:04.764
They see us.

439
00:33:08.086 --> 00:33:11.121
You have to go. I
can't. They'll kill you.

440
00:33:26.371 --> 00:33:29.739
You go out the door.
I'll drop to the floor.

441
00:33:29.791 --> 00:33:31.703
They're sharpshooters.
Michael. They won't miss.

442
00:33:31.727 --> 00:33:33.488
That's why you can't stay here.

443
00:33:33.512 --> 00:33:35.812
What's going on?
I'm coming. Doc!

444
00:33:35.880 --> 00:33:36.913
Go!

445
00:33:39.467 --> 00:33:40.951
(GUNS FIRING)

446
00:33:45.474 --> 00:33:47.140
(INMATES SHOUTING)

447
00:33:55.584 --> 00:33:57.884
<i>♪ (ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)</i>

448
00:34:10.982 --> 00:34:12.749
VERONICA: Who's this?

449
00:34:16.788 --> 00:34:18.288
That's my guy.

450
00:34:29.718 --> 00:34:31.118
Hey.

451
00:34:31.186 --> 00:34:33.436
Nice ride. Yeah. You like that?

452
00:34:34.138 --> 00:34:35.822
Cop auction. $300.

453
00:34:37.842 --> 00:34:39.425
You must be Veronica.

454
00:34:39.494 --> 00:34:41.644
Whoever tipped off the
cops about Lincoln Burrows

455
00:34:41.713 --> 00:34:43.680
called from this number.

456
00:34:45.684 --> 00:34:49.135
It wasn't an easy trace. I
hope you're not too bummed.

457
00:34:49.204 --> 00:34:50.504
Why? What's the problem?

458
00:34:50.572 --> 00:34:52.555
<i>FLETCH: It's a payphone.</i>

459
00:34:54.626 --> 00:34:56.359
This is it. 11th
and Constitution.

460
00:34:56.427 --> 00:34:58.107
Anyone could've made that call.

461
00:34:58.163 --> 00:35:01.965
Any one of the million people
who pass through here every day.

462
00:35:02.033 --> 00:35:03.499
That's empty.

463
00:35:05.220 --> 00:35:07.286
What about that?

464
00:35:07.355 --> 00:35:09.722
NICK: Federal Energy
Commission. That's interesting.

465
00:35:12.227 --> 00:35:13.643
Where you going?

466
00:35:13.712 --> 00:35:16.352
I'm gonna go see if this
guy knows what was in there.

467
00:35:20.502 --> 00:35:22.819
Excuse me.

468
00:35:22.888 --> 00:35:25.608
Do you know what was
in that space before you?

469
00:35:27.626 --> 00:35:29.092
Okay. Thanks.

470
00:35:33.348 --> 00:35:35.598
NICK: Hey. it was the
regional headquarters

471
00:35:35.667 --> 00:35:37.261
for a company called Ecofield.

472
00:35:37.285 --> 00:35:40.086
Terrence Steadman's
company? That's right.

473
00:35:41.723 --> 00:35:43.456
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

474
00:35:53.534 --> 00:35:55.374
Hello? <i>MAN: Veronica.</i>

475
00:35:56.537 --> 00:35:58.905
Who... who is this?

476
00:35:58.973 --> 00:36:03.443
<i>That's the problem. Veronica.
You ask too many questions.</i>

477
00:36:03.511 --> 00:36:07.346
<i>Now I have one for you. Is
Lincoln Burrows really worth it?</i>

478
00:36:08.584 --> 00:36:10.850
Here. give me the
phone. Who is this?

479
00:36:10.919 --> 00:36:14.120
<i>Nick Savrinn. I just
wanted to let you know.</i>

480
00:36:14.189 --> 00:36:17.057
<i>As of now. both of you are dead.</i>

481
00:36:17.125 --> 00:36:18.257
<i>(DIAL TONE DRONING)</i>

482
00:36:19.494 --> 00:36:21.178
Come on. let's go.

483
00:36:24.349 --> 00:36:27.834
<i>C.O.: (ON SPEAKER) All inmates
have one minute to return to their cells.</i>

484
00:36:27.902 --> 00:36:30.403
Michael! Michael!

485
00:36:31.473 --> 00:36:32.473
(GRUNTING)

486
00:36:32.541 --> 00:36:34.207
Whoa. whoa. whoa!

487
00:36:35.978 --> 00:36:38.778
I didn't touch your man. I
didn't touch him! Ask him.

488
00:36:38.847 --> 00:36:41.464
Things have changed
since we last met.

489
00:36:44.753 --> 00:36:47.754
Relax. partner.
I'm in on it now.

490
00:36:47.822 --> 00:36:50.890
The rabbit plan. Know
all about it. So's the CO.

491
00:36:58.099 --> 00:36:59.677
Why'd you take
Abruzzi down there?

492
00:36:59.701 --> 00:37:02.062
I didn't take him down there!
He was just. he just turned up!

493
00:37:02.086 --> 00:37:04.799
And the pedophile. he thinks he's
in. I know. <i>Tenemos un problema.</i>

494
00:37:04.823 --> 00:37:06.539
Shut up! Where's Michael?

495
00:37:07.542 --> 00:37:08.925
Where's Michael?

496
00:37:11.430 --> 00:37:13.946
Michael! Michael!

497
00:37:24.192 --> 00:37:26.392
<i>C.O.: (ON SPEAKER)
Final warning.</i>

498
00:37:38.256 --> 00:37:40.273
Where have you been?

499
00:37:40.342 --> 00:37:42.486
All over. Are you all
right? Yeah. Are you?

500
00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:44.344
Yes. Yes.

501
00:37:45.981 --> 00:37:47.181
LINCOLN: Move!

502
00:37:53.304 --> 00:37:55.171
(SARA SNIFFLING)

503
00:37:58.043 --> 00:38:00.123
Are you okay?
I'm okay. I'm okay.

504
00:38:01.646 --> 00:38:03.212
Bellick.

505
00:38:03.281 --> 00:38:06.182
She's walking.
That's a good sign.

506
00:38:06.250 --> 00:38:08.801
Yeah. astute observation.

507
00:38:08.870 --> 00:38:12.688
Maybe you'd like to share
that with the Governor.

508
00:38:12.757 --> 00:38:14.301
I was tense. I
was just trying...

509
00:38:14.325 --> 00:38:16.976
Next time you badmouth
me to one of my superiors.

510
00:38:17.045 --> 00:38:19.256
there are going to be
serious consequences.

511
00:38:19.280 --> 00:38:21.330
Do I make myself clear. Captain?

512
00:38:21.399 --> 00:38:22.432
Yes. sir.

513
00:38:22.501 --> 00:38:23.582
Good.

514
00:38:30.025 --> 00:38:31.224
Sara.

515
00:38:32.477 --> 00:38:34.527
Sara. Sara.

516
00:38:34.595 --> 00:38:36.729
Dad? Sara.

517
00:38:36.797 --> 00:38:39.999
Come on. Are you all right?
Are you okay? I told you.

518
00:38:40.068 --> 00:38:41.512
I told you when
you took this job.

519
00:38:41.536 --> 00:38:43.464
I knew something like
this was gonna happen.

520
00:38:43.488 --> 00:38:45.817
Didn't I? I knew something
like this was gonna happen.

521
00:38:45.841 --> 00:38:48.841
God. Dad. how about.
"I'm happy to see you alive"?

522
00:38:48.910 --> 00:38:50.655
Well. sweetheart. I
just want you to see

523
00:38:50.679 --> 00:38:52.628
what you're doing to yourself.

524
00:38:52.697 --> 00:38:56.432
I mean. there is nobody
that is forcing you to be here.

525
00:38:56.501 --> 00:38:58.802
I know. Thanks. Dad.

526
00:39:02.657 --> 00:39:05.358
All right. Let's
clean this mess up.

527
00:39:08.229 --> 00:39:09.762
(ALARM BLARING)

528
00:39:15.453 --> 00:39:16.514
What's going on?

529
00:39:16.538 --> 00:39:17.814
You won't believe
it. Fish. We did it.

530
00:39:17.838 --> 00:39:19.299
You've never
seen nothing like it.

531
00:39:19.323 --> 00:39:21.034
Those little Hooker
holes were right on.

532
00:39:21.058 --> 00:39:23.537
All right. Let's get everyone
out of here. Especially him.

533
00:39:23.561 --> 00:39:26.173
Getting him out of here. I'm
gonna take care of him myself.

534
00:39:26.197 --> 00:39:28.459
You're not going to kill him.
I'm not coming back here.

535
00:39:28.483 --> 00:39:30.199
It's over. We don't
need him no more.

536
00:39:30.268 --> 00:39:31.867
You're not gonna kill him.

537
00:39:31.936 --> 00:39:34.064
Are you so stupid you're gonna
let him walk out that front door?

538
00:39:34.088 --> 00:39:36.367
LINCOLN: That ain't for you
to decide! After all he's seen?

539
00:39:36.391 --> 00:39:38.641
After all he's seen?
After all he's seen?

540
00:39:38.709 --> 00:39:40.242
Get out.

541
00:39:40.311 --> 00:39:43.029
Keep your mouth
shut and turn left.

542
00:39:43.098 --> 00:39:44.330
Get out!

543
00:39:46.834 --> 00:39:49.853
If we have a problem.
we know where to find you.

544
00:39:49.921 --> 00:39:52.655
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

545
00:39:52.724 --> 00:39:55.809
Forget about it. Just
forget about it. all right?

546
00:40:15.863 --> 00:40:16.912
No!

547
00:40:39.554 --> 00:40:41.203
One for the team.

548
00:40:59.391 --> 00:41:02.024
Okay. So. this is the complete
list of the injured and dead.

549
00:41:02.093 --> 00:41:04.360
And it's the whole list? Yeah.

550
00:41:04.429 --> 00:41:06.195
Thank you very much.

551
00:41:09.333 --> 00:41:11.050
SARA: Thanks.

552
00:41:12.337 --> 00:41:13.603
Hey. Ron.

553
00:41:15.173 --> 00:41:16.840
Dr. Tancredi.

554
00:41:16.908 --> 00:41:18.619
Glad to see you
made it out alive.

555
00:41:18.643 --> 00:41:20.126
Yeah. me. too.

556
00:41:20.962 --> 00:41:22.629
Um. question.

557
00:41:22.697 --> 00:41:23.857
Mmm-hmm.

558
00:41:23.881 --> 00:41:25.893
Why'd your department
assign inmates on PI

559
00:41:25.917 --> 00:41:28.918
to do a toxic mold
removal project?

560
00:41:28.987 --> 00:41:32.021
What toxic mold project?

561
00:41:32.073 --> 00:41:34.607
In the. uh. the
crawlspace in A-Wing.

562
00:41:36.327 --> 00:41:40.062
PI didn't go there. And we'd
never assign inmates to do that.

563
00:41:42.417 --> 00:41:44.333
Okay. sorry. No problem.

564
00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:00.333
(CELL DOORS SLAMMING)

